## Testing Async UI with Delays

Some UI elements have intentional delays (e.g., Avatar fallback). Use `waitFor`:

```tsx
import { waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';

it('should render fallback after delay', async () => {
  render(<Avatar><AvatarFallback>Test</AvatarFallback></Avatar>);

  // Wait for element that appears after delay
  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.getByText('Test')).toBeInTheDocument();
  }, { timeout: 2000 });
});
```

